Geographical Information Systems
(syllabus)　
1. Course ID: 544M1370 
2. Professor: Feng-Tyan LIN
3. Time: 2:20-5:20 p.m., Monday
4. Classroom: Rm. 313,
Building of the College
 of Engineering
5. Objectives:
The objective of this course is to
familiarize students with the theory
of Geographic Information Systems (GIS), and its applications
on transportation planning,
engineering and management.  It will
also teach students the experience on practical operation.
The technology of GIS is fast-growing
and has been applied to many fields. 
Undoubtedly, it is also an important tool in land use and transportation
planning and management in regional
and urban scales.
This course will introduce basic
concepts, software architecture, system planning
and assessment methods of GIS, as well as the policies and implementation
issues of National GIS project in Taiwan.
6. Main subjects:
l   Introduction
l   Raster based data structure
l   Vector based data structure
l   Object oriented Relational Data Base
Management
l   Digitization and Preprocessing
l   Remote Sensing
l   Global Positioning Systems
l   Spatial Analyses
l   Spatial Statistics
l   Hardware and Network Environment
l   Land Surveying and Cadastral Map
l   GIS for Transportation
l   System Planning and Development for GIS
l   Project Management
l   Standards
l   Legal Issues
7. Language
So far this course is delivered in Mandarin; however, it can be in
English if it is necessary.
8. Further information in
Chinese can be found in http://Myweb.ncku.edu.tw/~ftlin/course/GIS/gisclass.htm  or you may contact with  me at ftlin@mail.ncku.edu.tw 
 
 





















